Standard and Poor's Corp said itaffirmed at A-1-plus commercial paper of Perkin-Elmer Corp.    S and P cited expectations of the firm to show sustainedlong-term profit improvement after a recent restructuring.    After two years of lackluster profitability and cuts inoperations, activities concentrated in promising product linesand reduced the firm's overall cost base, S and P noted.    It added that cash flow should strengthen due toanticipated improvement in asset management. Balance sheetstrength should continue with substantial liquidity and debt tototal capital at 22 pct as of July 31, S and P said. Reuter&#3;